defaultIn the UK, High Nature Value (HNV) farming – that which makes a particularly high contribution to the provision of environmental public goods - is mainly associated with low-intensity livestock systems, large
defaultly found in the uplands. 
defaultDespite the environmental benefits many such systems deliver, maintaining, or indeed even reaching, economic profitability remains a challenge. 
